SuicideRate_MachineLearning1

Milica Pajkic, Nuria Piller und Marco Rieder

2022-10-05

Suicide Rates in Finland, an analysis based on various factors

Suicide is a sensible topic and needs to be addressed in an empathical way. Behind each number and each case, is a story. This paper is analysing data from the statistical office of Finland. Trying to find evidence what factors are statisticly related is one of the goals. The main data source is this dataset

d.suicide_bancrupcy <- left_join(x=d.suicides_monthly, y= d.bancrupcy, by= "Month")

#remove rows without bankruptcy data (Before 1986)
d.suicide_bancrupcy <- na.omit(d.suicide_bancrupcy)
